      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know i should reach out, but what's the point? talking about it doesn't change the fact that i've failed. everyone expects me to just \"pivot\" or \"resilience\" my way through this, but there's nothing left to pivot with. it feels like there's this massive weight on my chest and the only way to actually get some peace is to just stop fighting. it feels more like an inevitable conclusion than a choice. everything is just so heavy.",
